3.caption_en:
Caption:
The slide "Digital Business Platforms ... A multi-sided business model" defines a platform as a business that connects two or more distinct groups to find, interact, exchange and co-create, leveraging network effects, data intelligence and infrastructure for long-term sustainability (attributed to Matthias Walter).

{
  "artifact_type": "slide",
  "title": "Digital Business Platforms ... A multi-sided business model",
  "definition": "Platform (n): \"A business that creates a positive impact for its users, society and our planet. It operates a physical or virtual place to help two or more different groups to find, interact, exchange & co-create with each other. It combines the strengths of network engagement (network effects), data intelligence and infrastructure for long term sustainability & success.\"",
  "bullets": [
    "find",
    "interact",
    "exchange",
    "co-create"
  ],
  "key_concepts": [
    "multi-sided platform",
    "network engagement",
    "network effects",
    "data intelligence",
    "infrastructure",
    "sustainability"
  ],
  "diagram": {
    "center_label": "Platform",
    "peripheral_nodes": [
      "Consumers",
      "Producers",
      "Partners",
      "Owner"
    ],
    "connections": "Nodes arranged around a central 'Platform' with bi-directional arrows (notably between Consumers and Producers)"
  },
  "author": "Matthias Walter",
  "layout": {
    "text_block": "left",
    "diagram": "right"
  },

}
